This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring October 10, 2016, as Columbus Day. It highlights the historical significance of Christopher Columbus's voyage to North America in 1492 and acknowledges the contributions made by Italian Americans to the United States. The proclamation also recognizes the suffering and broken promises experienced by Native Americans as a result of European colonization. The proclamation calls for observing Columbus Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities and for the display of the American flag on all public buildings.